because everyday we

00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:31.830
are flooded by so much
content in our phones.

00:03:31.830 --> 00:03:34.920
All the blogs that we
look at, all the comments,

00:03:34.920 --> 00:03:38.040
all the likes, all the
streaming, all the films.

00:03:38.040 --> 00:03:39.430
Everything.

00:03:39.430 --> 00:03:46.670
But unknowingly,
unknowingly we are so almost

00:03:46.670 --> 00:03:51.930
too inspired to a point where
we are losing ourselves,

00:03:51.930 --> 00:03:56.310
because we are taking in
everybody else's ideas--

00:03:56.310 --> 00:03:58.800
their thoughts, their voices.

00:03:58.800 --> 00:04:03.210
Therefore, if we are
not creative enough,

00:04:03.210 --> 00:04:07.320
we tend to what we call--

00:04:07.320 --> 00:04:09.580
we would ride on
other people's ideas.

00:04:09.580 --> 00:04:10.560
Let's twist.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:11.530
Let's tweak.

00:04:11.530 --> 00:04:14.950
Let's-- in [INAUDIBLE] we
would say [SPEAKING CHINESE]..

00:04:14.950 --> 00:04:17.459
But when we get into
a habit of that,

00:04:17.459 --> 00:04:23.250
we forget about being original,
being really creative,

00:04:23.250 --> 00:04:25.500
starting our own ideas.

00:04:25.500 --> 00:04:29.940
And to me that is very, very
dangerous, because if what

00:04:29.940 --> 00:04:34.080
you put out is no different
than the person next to you,

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:36.180
if what you contribute
to the company

00:04:36.180 --> 00:04:38.697
is just the same as
everybody else in the room,

00:04:38.697 --> 00:04:39.780
let me tell you something.

00:04:39.780 --> 00:04:42.810
Next year you won't be here.

00:04:42.810 --> 00:04:44.970
The company doesn't need you.

00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:48.000
Eventually the market
doesn't need you.

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:51.600
And the world--
they don't need you.

00:04:51.600 --> 00:04:55.500
So constantly ask
yourself how you

00:04:55.500 --> 00:05:00.320
can contribute more than
the person next to you.

00:05:00.320 --> 00:05:04.390
