for more than 22 years now.

00:05:04.390 --> 00:05:08.690
And I tell you, I ask myself
that question every damn day.

00:05:08.690 --> 00:05:10.230
Every day.

00:05:10.230 --> 00:05:13.380
Through music, through
film, through my shows,

00:05:13.380 --> 00:05:14.530
through my business.

00:05:14.530 --> 00:05:19.050
How do I be more creative?

00:05:19.050 --> 00:05:21.010
That is very, very hard.

00:05:21.010 --> 00:05:24.340
And maybe even in some fields,
it's getting harder and harder.

00:05:24.340 --> 00:05:27.640
Like in music, I would say
that it is harder for me

00:05:27.640 --> 00:05:33.040
now to compose a very
good piece of music

00:05:33.040 --> 00:05:37.540
than it was 15, 20 years
ago, because the time

00:05:37.540 --> 00:05:40.390
signatures or the
combinations of the notes

00:05:40.390 --> 00:05:42.370
are simply being taken up.

00:05:42.370 --> 00:05:44.920
It is harder to write
something original than now

00:05:44.920 --> 00:05:49.400
and have it not sound like that
it has been written by someone,

00:05:49.400 --> 00:05:52.570
sometime, like some
song back then.

00:05:52.570 --> 00:05:54.950
Because it's been done.

00:05:54.950 --> 00:05:57.010
But in our world,
that's what is happening

00:05:57.010 --> 00:06:00.610
is because all the ideas
are being voiced up.

00:06:00.610 --> 00:06:02.560
And we are seeing it.

00:06:02.560 --> 00:06:05.950
So if we don't voice out
loud enough, clear enough,

00:06:05.950 --> 00:06:10.000
soon enough, we are
actually behind.

00:06:10.000 --> 00:06:11.030
So I urge you--

00:06:11.030 --> 00:06:13.810
